OL,4,Cflowers on their son's grave, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FHe said: "The defendant armed himself
OL,8,Fwith a large kitchen knife from his
OL,9,Fhome address and he took it with him
OL,10,Fto the cemetery that morning while he
OL,11,Flaid in wait to attack Ann Blackwood,
OL,12,Frightly anticipating she would visit
OL,13,Fher son's grave that day."
OL,15,FHe said that Ms Blackwood arrived by
OL,16,Fbicycle at about 3.30pm and as she
OL,17,Fapproached the grave of their son, who
OL,18,Ftook his own life in 2003, Suter
OL,19,Fattacked her.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/10
