OL,3,CMan murdered ex-wife as she put
OL,4,Cflowers on their son's grave, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FMr O'Sullivan said Ms Blackwood had
OL,8,Fsuffered multiple stab wounds but no
OL,9,F"defensive wounds" which Home Office
OL,10,Fpathologist Dr Basil Purdue suggested
OL,11,Fmeant that she had been "taken by
OL,12,Fsurprise or overwhelmed by the attack".
OL,14,FThe court heard Suter had refused to
OL,15,Fattend the hearing and had told prison
OL,16,Fofficers at HMP Winchester that he
OL,17,Fbelieved the Newton hearing was
OL,18,F"inappropriate" because he had a
OL,19,F"moral right to a fair trial by jury,
OL,20,Fwithout duress".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
